OL,3,CLocal elections 2026: The Midlands
OL,4,Cresults
OL,6,FThe overnight results in the Midlands
OL,7,Fare mainly a story about Conservative
OL,8,Fcollapse - but there are signs Labour
OL,9,Fhas big problems too.
OL,11,FMany of the councils counted overnight
OL,12,Fwere Conservative-run anyway, so the
OL,13,FTories were always likely to take the
OL,14,Fbiggest hit.
OL,16,FIn Dudley, the Conservatives are still
OL,17,Fthe largest party but have lost
OL,18,Foverall control. In Newcastle-under-
OL,19,FLyme, the Tories lost the council to
OL,20,FReform UK, who now have a majority of
OL,21,Ffour.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778270754
OL,3,CLocal elections 2026: The Midlands
OL,4,Cresults
OL,6,FAnd in Tamworth, which had been Labour-
OL,7,Fheld, the council has slipped into no
OL,8,Foverall control.
OL,10,FWhile the picture is still emerging,
OL,11,Fwith no results yet from Birmingham,
OL,12,FSandwell, Coventry or Walsall - Reform
OL,13,FUK are topping the vote share in many
OL,14,Fplaces and turning that into seats,
OL,15,Fcutting through in areas that have
OL,16,Ftraditionally swung between Labour and
OL,17,Fthe Conservatives.
OL,19,FThe resultsJBirmingham -
OL,21,FCannock Chase -
